com.xhive.versioning.interfaces
Interface XhiveVersionIf

public interface XhiveVersionIf

Represents a version of a versionable object. Versionable objects are documents or blobs on which XhiveLibraryChildIf.makeVersionable() has been called.

(c) X-Hive Corporation B.V. (www.x-hive.com)

Since:
X-Hive/DB 2.0

Method Detail

abort

void abort()

Aborts the current version transaction.

After this call the version is no longer involved in a version transaction. abort() can only be called by the user that checked this version out or the Administrator.

Throws:
XhiveException.VERSION_NOT_CHECKED_OUT - when this version is not in versiontransaction.

checkInLibraryChild

XhiveVersionIf checkInLibraryChild(XhiveLibraryChildIf libraryChild)
Checkin a new library child as succesor of this version.

If this version already has a successor a new branch is created. Calling checkInLibraryChild() will end the version transaction that this version is in and will allow other users to create new versions from this version by calling checkOutLibraryChild().

Parameters:
libraryChild - The library child that represents the new version. This library child should be an XML document or a blob.
Returns:
The version object representing the new version that was created when checking in.
Throws:
XhiveException.VERSION_NOT_CHECKED_OUT - when this version is not checked out.
XhiveException.VERSION_CHECKED_OUT - when this version is checked out by other user.

checkIn

XhiveVersionIf checkIn(Document version)
Checkin a new document as succesor of this version.

If this version already has a successor a new branch is created. Calling checkIn() will end the version transaction that this version is in and will allow other users to create new versions from this version by calling checkOut().

Parameters:
version - The document that represents the new version. This document should be an X-Hive/DB DOM.
Returns:
The version object representing the new version that was created when checking in.
Throws:
XhiveException.VERSION_NOT_CHECKED_OUT - when this version is not checked out.
XhiveException.VERSION_CHECKED_OUT - when this version is checked out by other user.
XhiveException.WRONG_DOMIMPLEMENTATION_CHECKIN - when a document with the wrong DOMImplementation is checked in.

checkOutLibraryChild

XhiveLibraryChildIf checkOutLibraryChild()
Checkout this version to start a version transaction that will allow a user to create a new version.

Marks this version as checked out and returns a copy of the library child as it is at the moment of check out. The copy is created in the owner library of the version

After this call the version is involved in a version transaction, which means that it can not be checked out again, before the version transaction is either ended by checking in a new version or aborted by calling the abort method.

Returns:
Document copy of document represented by this version.
Throws:
XhiveException.VERSION_CHECKED_OUT - when this version already is checked out

Document checkOut()

Checkout this version to start a versiontransaction that will allow a user to create a new version.

Marks this version as checked out and returns a copy of the document as it is at the moment of checkOut.

After this call the version is involved in a version transaction, which means that it can not be checked out again, before the version transaction is either ended by checking in a new version or aborted by calling the abort method.

Returns:
Document copy of document represented by this version.
Throws:
XhiveException.VERSION_CHECKED_OUT - when this version already is checked out

checkOutLibraryChild

XhiveLibraryChildIf checkOutLibraryChild(XhiveLibraryIf library)

Same as checkOutLibraryChild() but use specified library to create the return child.

Marks this version as checked out and returns a copy of the library child as it is at the moment of check out. The copy is created in the library passed as an argument. If the library is null, no copy is created at all and the return value will be null.

After this call the version is involved in a version transaction, which means that it can not be checked out again, before the version transaction is either ended by checking in a new version or aborted by calling the abort method.

Parameters:
library - The library to be used to make copy of this version.
Returns:
A copy of the library child represented by this version.
Throws:
XhiveException.VERSION_CHECKED_OUT - when this version already is checked out

checkOut

Document checkOut(DOMImplementation impl)

Same as checkOut() but use DOMImplementation impl to create the return document.

Marks this version as checked out and returns a copy of the document as it is at the moment of checkOut. The copy is made using the DOMImplementation impl. If impl is null, the document will be a temporary document.

After this call the version is involved in a version transaction, which means that it can not be checked out again, before the version transaction is either ended by checking in a new version or aborted by calling the abort method.

Parameters:
impl - DOMImplementation impl to be used to make copy of this version.
Returns:
Document copy of document represented by this version.
Throws:
XhiveException.VERSION_CHECKED_OUT - when this version already is checked out
See Also:
XhiveSessionIf.createTemporaryDocument()

getAsLibraryChild

XhiveLibraryChildIf getAsLibraryChild()
Get the library child from the version without using a version transaction. The library child returned is a temporary library child and cannot be used after the transaction this library child was returned in has ended. If you want to use (for example add it to a library) the returned library child then use getAsLibraryChild(XhiveLibraryIf) and pass the library you want to add the library child to. This library child can be changed but not checked in.

getAsDocument

Document getAsDocument()

Get the document from the version without using a version transaction. The document returned is a temporary document a can not be used after the transaction this document was returned in has ended. If you want to use(for example add it to a library) the returned document then use getAsDocument(DOMImplementation impl) and pass the library you want to add the document to. This document can be changed but not checked in.

getId

java.lang.String getId()

Get this version's Id.

This Id is assigned to the version by the system and cannot be changed.

The Id of a new version is 1 added to the last number of its predecessors Id when a new version is created without creating a new branch.

So 1.6 follows 1.5 and 1.8.4.5 follows 1.8.4.4 and so on.

When a new branch is created (see XhiveBranchIf) the Id of a new version is the first even number available added to the Id of the version where the branch is created from to indicate the Id of the new branch and a 1 is added after that to indicate that this new version is the first version of the new branch.

So creating a branch from 1.5 (1.6 already exists) creates a version with Id 1.5.2.1
2 is added to 1.5 because it is the first available even number (there are no other branches created from version 1.5 yet)
1 is added to 1.5.2 to indicate that the new version is the first in this branch.

When a new branch is created from version 1.8 a version with the Id 1.8.6.1 is created because 6 is the first even number after 4.

Returns:
The Id of this version.
